I"ô<p><a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/body-movement-supports-spatial-reasoning">Spatial reasoning</a> forces the individual to abstract away from features perceived through individual modalities, such as brightness and loudness, and derive an <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/physical-and-conceptual-spaces-are-coded-in-the-same-region">independent spatial representation</a>. Due to this, spatial reasoning is conceptually located at the confluence of all the bodily senses.</p>
